1. $ export "environmentname"
Exports the environment variable

2. # ls *.jpg | xargs -n1 -i cp {} /external-hard-drive/directory
Copy all images to external harddisk

3. # find / -name *.jpg -type f -print | xargs tar -cvzf images.tar.gz
Search all jpg images in the system and archieve it.

